<HEAD>Billy Graham Sees Better Future For China's Christians</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 American evangelist <PERSON> Billy </PERSON> <PERSON> Graham </PERSON> said today he was encouraged by the growing but still limited religious freedom in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> and was optimistic about <ORGANIZATION> Christianity </ORGANIZATION>'s future in the communist nation. <PERSON> Graham </PERSON> also said he had been unable to substantiate reports that a Chinese itinerant preacher who spreads the Gospel in defiance of the state-sponsored church was arrested after arriving in <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION> to hear the Southern Baptist minister. <PERSON> Graham </PERSON>, speaking at a news conference in this British colony at the end of his 16-day visit to <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>, said he contacted high-level <LOCATION> Chinese </LOCATION> authorities and the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Embassy to get information about the reported arrest of <PERSON> Xu </PERSON> <PERSON> Yongzhe </PERSON>, but received neither verification nor denial of the report. `` My wife and I have been praying daily for him if he indeed has been detained,'' <PERSON> Graham </PERSON> said. He said he could not intervene in the matter but could `` relate my feelings about it and I have already done that.'' He did not elaborate. According to the director of the <ORGANIZATION> Chinese </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Research </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Hong </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kong </LOCATION>, Xu was arrested April 16 after traveling to <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION> from central <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> to hear <PERSON> Graham </PERSON>. The center has links to Protestants in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> who worship in unofficial `` house churches.'' A source in <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION> with links to preachers outside the state-sanctioned church has confirmed Xu's arrest. <PERSON> Graham </PERSON> said he did not know <PERSON> Xu </PERSON> and had not heard of him before his reported de