<DATELINE>ATHENS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The government said today it did n't know the leader of an Armenian terrorist group who was assassinated outside his <LOCATION> Athens </LOCATION> home had lived in <LOCATION> Greece </LOCATION> for the past year. <PERSON> Agop </PERSON> <PERSON> Agopian </PERSON> was gunned down before dawn Thursday as he waited for a taxi in front of his suburban apartment. Police sources said <PERSON> Agopian </PERSON> lived in <LOCATION> Greece </LOCATION> for at least a year, posing as a Lebanese businessmen. He was founder and chief of the Armenian <ORGANIZATION> Secret </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> for the Liberation of <LOCATION> Armenia </LOCATION>. `` Authorities in <LOCATION> Greece </LOCATION> did n't know his identity,'' government spokesman <PERSON> Sotiris </PERSON> <PERSON> Kostopoulos </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Agopian </PERSON> also carried a South <LOCATION> Yemen </LOCATION> diplomatic passport in the name of <PERSON> Abdul </PERSON> <PERSON> Mohammed </PERSON> <PERSON> Kasim </PERSON>. <PERSON> Kostopoulos </PERSON> said <PERSON> Agopian </PERSON>, who was not registered as a diplomat here, had not been working in <LOCATION> Greece </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Agopian </PERSON> and a woman identified as his sister-in-law were standing in front of <PERSON> Agopian </PERSON>'s home when two masked men emerged from a car. One man shot <PERSON> Agopian </PERSON> twice with a sawed-off shotgun and fired again when the victim tried to run. The assailants fled. The woman was unhurt. There was no immediate claim of responsibility for the killing. The assassination could have been the work of a rival extremist group, said Armenian sources in <LOCATION> Athens </LOCATION> who spoke on condition of anonymity. Police at first identified the victim as 39-year-old <PERSON> Abdul </PERSON> <PERSON> Mohammed </PERSON> <PERSON> Kashim </PERSON>, born in <LOCATION> Aden </LOCATION>, based on the <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Yemeni </LOCATION> diplomatic p