<HEAD>Iran Reports More Than 10 Drug Smugglers Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Iranian Revolutionary Guards killed more than 10 heavily armed drug smugglers in the eastern province of <LOCATION> Kerman </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Tehran </LOCATION> radio reported Thursday. It quoted authorities as saying the guards ambushed a group of smugglers stationed in the mountains southeast of the city of <LOCATION> Kerman </LOCATION>, the provincial capital. During the fighting, the report said, more than 10 of the smugglers were killed. The radio did not give an exact date for the incident. According to the report, the smugglers carried anti-aircraft weapons, offensive missiles, radios and other weapons, and killed a number of Revolutionary Guards in the skirmishes. The report did not say what type of drugs were being smuggled, but Iranian media have recently reported the arrests of a number of heroin dealers. The drugs were smuggled across <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>'s eastern border with <LOCATION> Afghanistan </LOCATION> or <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION>.
