,'' he said of the state's law, `` it goes beyond this -LRB- federal proposal -RRB- and in other ways it does n't.'' <PERSON> Gureghian </PERSON> said the state defines a plant closing as laying off 90 percent of the work force at a plant. A `` partial closing,'' <PERSON> Gureghian </PERSON> said, is `` a permanent cessation of a major, discreet portion'' of a company or division. The reported plans for Cullinet layoffs would not apply to either definition, he said.
