 <PERSON> Cohon </PERSON> said. `` There will be many more.'' Soviets will be able to buy a <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mac </ORGANIZATION>, the chain's double-patty hamburger sandwich, for about 2 rubles, or roughly $ 3. The first McDonald's in the Soviet capital is expected to open on Gorky Street next year, <PERSON> Cohon </PERSON> said. But nobody will say where. `` We do n't want to create any lines,'' <PERSON> Zharov </PERSON> said with a smile.
