<BYLINE>By LEE GOULD</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ethics </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> criticized Sen. <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Durenberger </PERSON> on Friday for discussing an espionage case in public last year, but stopped short of recommending disiplinary action against the <ORGANIZATION> Minnnesota </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION>. The committee said the remarks by <PERSON> Durenberger </PERSON>, the immediate past chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Intelligence </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, had `` jeopardized the mutual confidence which must exist between the <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> and the intelligence community.'' `` The ethics committee has determined that your statements gave the appearance that you were disclosing sensitive national security information,'' <PERSON> Durenberger </PERSON> was told. The Ethics <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> investigation centered on comments <PERSON> Durenberger </PERSON> made at an event sponsored by the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Israel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Public </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Affairs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Palm </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Beach </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>, on March 15, 1987. Some members of the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> were said to have been angered by <PERSON> Durenberger </PERSON>'s reported disclosure to the group that then-CIA Director <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Casey </PERSON> in 1982 had `` changed the rules'' under which allies did not spy on each other by recruiting an <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> military officer to spy on <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> for the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Durenberger </PERSON> later denied he had revealed any clas