<HEAD>Trade Deficit Narrows Sharply</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>'s merchandise trade deficit narrowed unexpectedly and sharply in March to a seasonally adjusted $ 1.61 billion from $ $ 2.48 billion in February, the government said Friday. However, the deficit was much wider than the deficit a year ago, which came to $ 703 million. <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>'s total trade deficit also narrowed sharply. That figure, which includes merchandise, services, overseas investment earnings and transfer payments, showed a $ 478 million deficit in March compared with a $ 1.35 billion deficit in February and a $ 556 million surplus in March 1987, the <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Industry </ORGANIZATION> said. Private economists had predicted a merchandise deficit of $ 1.1 billion and a total deficit of $ 1.02 billion for March.
